The entire Benin City will be locked down for the 8th Oba of Benin Golf Tournament billed to tee-off on Friday (today) January 14 through Saturday, January 15, 2022 at Benin Club Golf Section (BCGS), Edo State. The Oba Cup tournament being one of the biggest golf event in the South-South Nigeria will feature over two hundred amateur and professional golfers from various clubs in the country. The professional golfers teed off their section on Wednesday and ended on Thursday to the delight of the Captain of the Benin Club Golf Section, Mr. Mayer Ologbosere. AFCON 2021: Ruthless Cameroon Beat Ethiopia To Book Last 16… …Rep Member Urges Super Eagles To Sustain Tempo The captain stated further that Friday is day one and will feature handicaps 0-28 men, and 0-36 ladies as well as all veterans and super veterans, while the cocktail party is slated for 6pm same day. He added that handicaps 0-18 men as well as handicaps 0-28 ladies and all guests will exercise their skills at the event on Saturday, while the dinner and presentation of trophies and prizes will be held at 6pm same day. Similarly, Chairman of the Tournament Organising Committee, Barrister Peace Anunah confirmed that His Royal Majesty, Oba Ewuare II, Oba of Benin Kingdom will perform the ceremonial tee-off on Saturday at 9am. He further stated that they golfers are expected from Ibori Golf and Country Club, Asaba; Ogunnu Golf Resort, Warri; Sapele Athletic Club, Delta State. UBTH Golf Club, Benin City; IBB International Golf and Country Club, Abuja; Ikoyi Golf Club, Lagos; Arsenal Golf Club, Owerri, Imo State; and many others. “Winners in each category will take home trophies and other prizes, while individual performances such as longest drive, and nearest the pin will be rewarded,” he concluded.